OSX Terminal.app
----------------

* View -> Show tab bar
* Preferences -> Settings -> Copy Homebrew to Kimo
  * Make default
  * Uncheck "Blink cursor"
  * Font: Monaco Regular 11pt.
  * Antialias text
  * Keyboard -> "Use option as meta key"
  * Keyboard -> Uncheck "Scroll alternate screen"
  * Advanced -> Uncheck "Audible bell"
  * Window -> Background -> Opacity: 100%
  * Shell -> When the shell exits: Close the window
* Preferences -> startup
  * New tables open with: Default working Directory
* Disable copy/paste preserving formatting: defaults write com.apple.Terminal CopyAttributesProfile com.apple.Terminal.no-attributes

Copy On Select
* https://gist.github.com/hetima/51b71091aedf622f61f7
* http://www.culater.net/software/SIMBL/SIMBL.php
* http://superuser.com/questions/62609/how-can-i-copy-on-select-in-the-os-x-terminal-like-putty-does
  "git clone https://github.com/genki/terminalcopyonselect.git
cd terminalcopyonselect
open TerminalCopyOnSelect.xcodeproj
# edit Info.plist and set SIMBLTargetApplications's MaxBundleVersion to 400, which is enough for MacOSX Yosemite's Terminal.app
# hit build, and it will copy TerminalCopyOnSelect.bundle under it's proper place: ~/Library/Application Support/SIMBL/Plugins"
* Move to /Library/Application Support/SIMBL/Plugins
